<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
	<body>
		<h1>Gadget Editor Tools</h1>
		<h2>Content</h2>
		<div class="toc">
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="#GadgetArtifact">Gadget Artifact</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<h2 id="GadgetArtifact">Gadget Artifact</h2>		
        <p>
        To create a gadget, right click on the CApp project and select <strong>Gadget</strong> from the 
        menu. 
        </p>
		<p>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
			<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget1.png"></img>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
		</p>
		<p>
		There are three ways to create a gadget.    
		</p>
		<ol>
			<li>New Gadget</li>
			<li>Import Gadget from File System</li>
			<li>Import Gadget from Registry</li>
		</ol>
		<p>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
			<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget2.png"></img>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
		</p>

			<p>With the <strong>New Gadget</strong> option, you will get a simple gadget.xml with the specified name. At the same time, 
			you can upload a <strong>Gadget</strong> file or any file with the extension of <strong>.xml</strong> from the 
			file system or from the registry.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget3.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>
			
			<p>With the <strong>Import Gadget from Registry</strong>, you can browse resources of the registry instance that you 
			have already created or you can create a new registry instance as well. After selecting the registry instance, click on 
			<strong>Browse</strong> to browse resources in registry. 
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget4.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>	
			
			<p>Select the CApp project you want to create <strong>Gadget</strong> and click <strong>Finish</strong>.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget5.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>	
			
			<p>Now you will see new Gadget artifact is created under the selected CApp project.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget6.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>
			<p>When you double click on the <strong>gadget.xml</strong> file, it will open in the gadget editor. 
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/gadget7.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>			
									
	</body>
</html>
